Thailand Stocks: Khon Kaen, PTT, Samart Telcoms, Total Access

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-07-20T09:52:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/bank-of-ayudhya-khon-kaen-siam-commercial-thai-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close in Bangkok.  The SET Index rose for a fifth day, climbing 4.6 points, or
0.4 percent, to 1,101.37, the highest since April 25.  Khon Kaen Sugar Industry Pcl (KSL)  , a Thai sugar miller,
gained 2.2 percent to 14 baht, the biggest rise since June 10.
 Khon Kaen  Sugar plans to boost sales of ethanol in 2012 to as
much as 100 million liters, from 40 million liters this year,
the Thai-language Kao Hoon newspaper said, citing Chalush
Chinthammit, a company director. Chalush was not available for
comment after a call to his office.  PTT Pcl (PTT)  , the country’s largest energy company,
added 1.8 percent to 346 baht. PTT and its units plan to invest
1 trillion baht ($33.5 billion) between 2012 and 2016 to expand
in Thailand and overseas, President Prasert Bunsumpun said.  Samart Telcoms Pcl (SAMTEL)  , a telecommunications
service provider, jumped 4.9 percent to 12.8 baht, the largest
increase since April 22. The company won a contract valued 289.6
million baht from a state-owned phone company, it said in a
regulatory filing.  Total Access Communication Pcl (DTAC)  , the nation’s
second-biggest mobile phone company, jumped 6 percent to 61.75
baht, extending yesterday’s 3.6 percent gain. Thailand’s
commerce ministry won’t take legal action against Total Access
over allegations that the company breached foreign-ownership
limits, Banyong Limprayoonwong, head of the ministry’s Business
Development Department, told reporters yesterday.  The commerce ministry’s decision is “positive” for Total
Access,  Asia  Plus Securities Pcl in a report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 